{
  "texts": [
    "According to Panda et al. (2024), microgrids are self-supporting generation sources that incorporate renewable energy sources.",
    "However, managing the batteries' charge-discharge level is essential while considering the devices' smoother long-term efficiency and reliability.",
    "An RL-based strategy can provide instructions for generating pulse width modulation signals in grid-connected inverters.",
    "These inverters possess bidirectional power exchange capabilities, enabling them to regulate the direction and magnitude of power flow between the battery and the utility grid, and the agents are trained on real-world sensor readings in practical scenarios to govern the inverter's operations, thereby managing the battery's charging and discharging processes.",
    "According to the authors, previous approaches used Deep Q-learning-based methods with PER."
  ]
}